problem:
For integers $n$, let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
n^2 & \text{ if }n\text{ is odd}, \\
n^2 - 4n - 1 & \text{ if }n\text{ is even}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(f(f(f(f(4)))))$.

For complex numbers $z$, let \[f(z) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
z^{2}&\text{ if }z\text{ is not real}, \\
z+2 &\text{ if }z\text{ is real}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f(i)+f(1)+f(-1)+f(-i)$.

solution:
Using the distributive property, we can expand this to get \begin{align*}
(x^{22}&-3x^{5} + x^{-2} - 7)\cdot(5x^4)\\
&=(x^{22})(5x^4)+(-3x^5)(5x^4)+(x^{-2})(5x^4)-7(5x^4)\\
&=5x^{26}-15x^9+5x^2-35x^4\\
&=\boxed{5x^{26}-15x^9-35x^4+5x^2}.
\end{align*}

problem:
